title: Trolls Left Negative Rotten Tomatoes Reviews On Unreleased Captain Marvel - Without Success
body:
Trolls Left Negative Rotten Tomatoes Reviews On Unreleased Captain Marvel – Without Success

Credit: Marvel Studios

You know that when the misogynists and bigots come out to play, it’s because they’re angry – and nothing makes them angrier than women dominating in a “traditionally male” environment.

Enter Captain Marvel. We are only a few days away from the release of Marvel’s first solo female-lead superhero film (only took em ten years), which will hit cinemas in both the US and the UK…

blog.name: callmepolaris
blog.title: a little favor? Call me Polaris.
blog.description:
Hello there,
Welcome to my blog. I support diversity, so I don't mind how you live your life, I accept you...Except if you are an overbearing unkind arse! Get out!

I love photography and philosophy, so you will find some cool pics and random quotes.

I love powerful scenes, with strong women and a nice script.

I'm not a huge fan of movie theaters. My anxiety hates a room full of strangers and loud sounds...Ironically, because I have been working in the music industry for at least 15 years.

I'm such an easy-going person, if you call me 'ignorant' or wtvr; name calling does not make me read your argument...Try to educate me, I'm open for it.

That's not all, but that's it for now.

summary: Every person making their lame "the cat is a better actor/more likeable than Brie Larson" jokes is weak and would 100% get...
body:
Every person making their lame “the cat is a better actor/more likeable than Brie Larson” jokes is weak and would 100% get devoured by Goose’s Flerken tentacle maw if she (the cat) heard them.

In other words, you’re not being funny or original at all and your comments are just an irritant to scroll through. Be excited for Goose, by all means. She is amazing and I’m personally super excited to see if we get a moment with her and Rocket in Endgame like in the comics. But stop being shitheads. Not that I think y'all will listen. You’re the same people who go on Rotten Tomatoes and talk shit about the movie without even having seen it because you’re pissed Brie is an outspoken feminist. (Almost all early reviews of the movie are GLOWING by the way so 🖕)
